Frank Blake - Wikipedia





















 






Frank Blake

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

For the college football coach, see Frank Blake (American football). For other people of the same name, see Francis Blake (disambiguation).


Frank Blake


Born
Frank Blake
(1949-07-30) July 30, 1949 (age 67)
Boston, Massachusetts, U.S.


Occupation
CEO


Francis Stanton "Frank" Blake (born July 30, 1949) is an American businessman and lawyer, who was the chairman and CEO of The Home Depot from January 2007 to May 2014. Prior to this he worked for the U.S. Department of Energy and General Electric. He was a longtime protégé of Robert Nardelli.



Contents


1 Education and family
2 Legal career
3 Management

3.1 CEO of Home Depot


4 References



