               Title: Senior Account Executive
Blake William Francis's Experience
Title: Senior Account Executive
               Company: Mongonet Inc.
Job Details
               Company Size: $1 mil to less than $5 mil - Employee Range: Less than 25. Founded in 1999, MongoNet® is a privately held corporation headquartered in San Francisco, California. The company has developed a massively-scalable patented technology and communications service called MongoFAXÔ. The service makes paper as versatile, ubiquitous and easy as email, providing a superior new channel of paper delivery over existing options such as courier, overnight, mail and traditional fax. The service leverages a base of 130 Million installed fax machines coupled with the world's 500+ Million email users.  We live in a digital world, yet ironically the Internet itself has fostered increased paper consumption due to unprecedented access to information and the ability to share files that get printed. The United States consumption of office paper increased by 15% from 1995 to 2000. 420 Billion pages of traditional fax were sent worldwide in 2001. It is predicted that traditional fax traffic will increase to 650 Billion pages by the year 2005. This represents approximately $35 Billion in long distance telecom charges paid by fax senders every year.  MongoFAXÔ bypasses these long distance telecom charges while enabling people to digitally deliver paper documents as PDF files from ordinary fax machines* to any email address in the world - with no added hardware and no added software.  MongoFAXÔ is ideal for organizations in paper intensive (contract intensive) market verticals such as insurance, legal, banking, transportation, title companies, trust companies, real estate, financial, health, biotech, government and other organizations.
